In the Matter of Gilbert William DAVIS, Bankrupt. Gilbert William DAVIS, Appellant, v. HOUSEHOLD FINANCE CORPORATION, Appellee. No. 6817. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Nov. 30, 1938.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellee, counsel for appellant consenting thereto, it is now here ordered, adjudged and decreed by this court that this cause be docketed in this court and that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
